is the favour of God, whose guide is
this perfect way, the word of GOD:
which is therfore called a way, because
it leads us to our journeyes end; and a
perfect way, because the Authour of it
is the abstract of all perfection; because

it sufficiently containes in it all things
requisite to bring us to perfection both
of body and soule, both of grace and
glory; and lastly, because it makes those
perfect that walk in it, at least in regard
of endeavour, and the severall parts of
perfection, though not the degrees: as,
a childe may bee said to bee a perfect
man, in that hee hath all the parts of a
