yet David kept himselfe in his uprightness:

hee hasted not by any indirect attempt
(as did his sonne Absolon afterwards
against himselfe) to seeke his
owne revenge, nor to displace the
King and his seed, which hee knew in
time were to be remoued; but patiently
waited upon God, doing his will:
yea, when God two severall times had
