he sharply rebuked Abner for guarding
the Kings person so weakly, at the other.
Thus did this holy man wisely
carry himselfe in the perfect way of patience
and loyalty to his cruell Prince,
and persecuting father in law, till God
himselfe (by the way that he appointed)
had set him in the Kings seat.
