his knowledge of foraine States &amp; languages;
as for his fidelity: Any of the
rest, nay all the rest without it, serving
only to make a servant more disposed &amp;
more able too, as well for the plotting
as the acting of villany; wheras fidelity,
having joyned with it but some few of
the rest in a mediocrity, makes him serviceable
in a good degree.
            This is the commendation of Moses,
