signet upon his finger, yet would hee pluck
him thence, Ieremy 22. 24. And as his
practice is, so is his precept: Ye shall haue
one lawe, it shall be as well for the stranger,
as the borne in the countrey. The stranger
if hee deserve favour, must have it
as much as if hee were borne in the
countrey: and hee that is borne in the
countrey must be punished as severely

as if hee were a stranger.
